cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CV

The paper proposes a new method for network anomaly detection using autoencoders, which is a common technique in machine learning and falls under the category of deep learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with cybersecurity and network security, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of neural networks and unsupervised learning also suggests that it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper involves data augmentation and reconstruction error, which are common techniques in computer vision, suggesting that it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the use of unsupervised learning and neural networks for anomaly detection suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
